  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-nduja-tomato-risotto-with-pine-nuts-and-basil-oil/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine</strong> <strong>nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once toasted, set aside for later and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-nduja-tomato-risotto-with-pine-nuts-and-basil-oil/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> <strong>mix</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong> in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-nduja-tomato-risotto-with-pine-nuts-and-basil-oil/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onion is softening, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> and your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-nduja-tomato-risotto-with-pine-nuts-and-basil-oil/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and your <strong>plant based 'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>arborio</strong> <strong>rice </strong>and <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-nduja-tomato-risotto-with-pine-nuts-and-basil-oil/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks, then grind the <strong>chopped basil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a paste and add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>basil oil</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle & mortar, chop the basil very finely and mix with the olive oil</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-nduja-tomato-risotto-with-pine-nuts-and-basil-oil/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, stir the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>veg</strong> through the risotto with your <strong>umami</strong> <strong>seasoning</strong>, a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>plant-based 'Nduja & tomato risotto</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-nduja-tomato-risotto-with-pine-nuts-and-basil-oil/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>plant-based 'Nduja & tomato risotto</strong> topped with the <strong>toasted pine nuts</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>basil oil </strong>over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
